# Contributing to {{ project_name }}

Thanks for contributing. `{{ project_name }}` is owned by the **{{ department.name }}**
department ({% for u in users %}{{ u.name }}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %})
and follows the Ramboll Developer Platform golden-path standards. These standards are
**non-negotiable** — they are what make the service maintainable and green.

## Branching model

Three long-lived branches:

- **`main`** — production. Protected: PR + review + green checks required.
- **`dev`** — integration. **PRs target this branch.**
- **`staging`** — pre-production validation.

All work happens on short-lived branches cut from `dev`, named **exactly** one of:

| Prefix | Use | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `feature/` | New behaviour | `feature/PROJ-142-health-endpoint` |
| `bug/` | Defect fix | `bug/PROJ-188-slug-empty-input` |
| `hotfix/` | Urgent production fix | `hotfix/PROJ-201-uvicorn-crash` |

The pattern is `<type>/<ticket>-<slug>`. Anything that does not match is
**rejected by the branch-name check** in CI — rename your branch.

## Commits

Use [**Conventional Commits**](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
feat: add /health endpoint
fix: handle empty input in slugify
docs: expand the runbook recovery section
test: add property test for word_count invariance
```

## Pull requests

1. Open the PR **into `dev`**.
2. A review is required, and **CODEOWNERS** (`@{{ department.team_slug }}`{% for u in users %} `@{{ u.github_login }}`{% endfor %}) must approve.
3. The **Build / Test / Validate** checks must all be **green** before merge.
4. Fill in the PR template checklist.

## Quality gates (what CI enforces)

- **Property tests:** every new public, pure function ships with **at least one
  property test** (Hypothesis). Treat a shrinking counterexample as a real bug.
- **Clean code:** small, single-responsibility, fully-typed functions with
  docstrings. Must pass `ruff check`, `black --check .`, and `mypy`.
- **Docs:** `mkdocs build --strict` must pass; update `docs/` when behaviour changes.

Run them locally before pushing:

```bash
ruff check .
black --check .
mypy
pytest
mkdocs build --strict
```

## CI governance

**CI must always reference the reusable workflows — no ad-hoc pipelines.** Do not
copy-paste pipeline steps into this repository. If the pipeline needs to change,
the change belongs in the central reusable workflow so every service benefits.

